LMS v2.0 — Full-Stack Rebuild Prompt
Build a fully functional Learning Management System (LMS) web application with three user roles: Admin, Teacher, and Student. The application must be production-quality, with a classic, professional UI and deep functionality across all roles.

Tech Stack

Frontend: React + Tailwind CSS
Backend: Python (FastAPI or Flask) + SQLAlchemy ORM
Database: PostgreSQL (or SQLite for development)
Auth: JWT-based authentication with role-based access control (RBAC)
File Storage: Local filesystem or S3-compatible storage for uploads
Charts: Chart.js or Recharts for analytics
Rich Text: TipTap or Quill.js for course content editing


UI/UX Design Rules (Strict)

Color palette: White, off-white (#F9F9F9), light grey (#F0F0F0), mid grey (#9CA3AF), dark grey (#374151), near-black (#111827). One single accent color: a muted navy (#1E3A5F) or slate blue (#3B5998) for primary actions only.
No gradients, no glassmorphism, no neon, no glow effects, no sharp color bursts.
Buttons must look like real physical buttons: solid background, 1px border, subtle box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.08), slight darkening on hover, scale-down on active click.
Typography: Inter or System UI font stack. Clear size hierarchy: 13px labels, 15px body, 18px section headings, 24px page titles. Font weight 400/500 only — no heavy 700 weights in body text.
Spacing: Generous padding, consistent 8px grid system. Cards use 16–24px internal padding.
Borders: 1px solid #E5E7EB on cards, inputs, tables. No thick or colored borders.
Dark mode toggle: Fully supported. Dark mode uses #0F172A background, #1E293B card surfaces, #94A3B8 secondary text.
Sidebar: Collapsible, with icon-only collapsed state. Active route highlighted with accent color left border and light background tint.
Tables: Striped rows (#FAFAFA alternate), sticky headers, sortable columns, pagination.
Forms: Floating labels or clean top-labels. Input focus ring: 2px solid #1E3A5F. Validation errors shown inline in red (#DC2626) below the field.
Animations: Only functional micro-interactions — skeleton loaders for data fetching, 150ms ease transitions on hover states, smooth sidebar collapse. No decorative animations.
Modals: Centered, white card on a rgba(0,0,0,0.4) overlay. Escape key closes them. Always include a visible close button.
Toast notifications: Bottom-right corner, auto-dismiss after 4 seconds. Success = green tint, Error = red tint, Info = blue tint — all muted, not saturated.


Database Models

Design and implement all of the following SQLAlchemy models with proper relationships, foreign keys, and indexes:
User, Tenant (organization), Course, Enrollment, Lesson, LessonModule (content blocks), Assignment, Submission, Quiz, QuizQuestion, QuizOption, QuizAttempt, Grade, Attendance, Resource (file/link library), Message (direct messaging), Notification, Announcement, DiscussionBoard, DiscussionPost, DiscussionReply, Badge, UserBadge, StudyGroup, StudyGroupMember, Note (private per-user per-lesson), AuditLog, SubscriptionTier, CalendarEvent

Authentication & Authorization

JWT access tokens (15-min expiry) + refresh tokens (7-day expiry), stored in httpOnly cookies.
Role guards on every route: admin_required, teacher_required, student_required.
Tenancy isolation: all queries scoped to tenant_id automatically via a middleware layer.
Password hashing with bcrypt. Email verification on signup. Password reset via time-limited token link.


